  "Sumner Redstone is the controlling shareholder of the new ViacomCBS; the two companies completed a merger in early December 2019.",
  "Redstone's father founded the cinema chain now known as National Amusements in 1936; Redstone took over in 1954.",
  "He acquired control of Viacom in 1987 and spun off CBS in 2006.",
  "Redstone's daughter, Shari, serves as the non-executive chair of ViacomCBS."
